            <description pref="true" source="Metropolitan Museum of Art online. www.metmuseum.org ; Page: accessed 13 December 2006.">
                <text>The artist was working at the court of Shah ‘Abbas the Great (reigned 1588-1629); this work shows his renowned inventive palette and calligraphic line. The lovers are drawn as inextricably bound together, merged volumes confined within one outline.</text>
                <author>
                    <name refid="131347215" type="corporate" vocab="viaf">Visual Resources Association</name>
